Github - remote code repo - it will have only your code and Proeprties file

git  - versioncontrol management tool --->


Local system - folder ---> git ------> Repo



Git Comments:

git and github setup
	$ git config --global user.name "John Doe"
	$ git config --global user.email johndoe@example.com
Stesp - 1

	Clone Repository from Github -
		pre requisite - create a folder in your local machine 
			mkdir foldername
		git clone <reponamelink - example - https://github.com/sathishrpt24/gitDemo.git>

Step -2:
	A new code has been written and we need to push the code to Github
		Staging - adding a newfile or changed details to git
		commit - Creatae a version
		push - send the details to remote repository
		
		$git status - this will give you a staus of the file which is being changed

Step - 3:
		$git add.*
Step -4:
	$ git commit -m "Message"
	
Step - 5:

	$ git push















		
		